name: Dance All Night with a Bottle in My Hand
Tennessee Mountain Fox Chase
comments: Vance's Tennessee Breakdowners recorded six sides for Okeh on Thursday, September 22, 1927.  This was titled "Washington County Fox Chase" at the sessions but went unissued.  When it was finally released in 1972 by County Records it was titled "Tennessee Mountain Fox Chase" and   that's how it's known today.  It was re-released in 1992 on the Root n' Blues compilation with the original title.
